Differentially Private PSO-Optimized MLP for IoT Intrusion Detection
README
Title
Privacy-Preserving Intrusion Detection Using Particle Swarm Optimization and Differentially Private Deep Learning for IoT Networks
________________________________________
1. Project Overview
This repository presents a reproducible implementation of a Differentially Private (DP) Multi-Layer Perceptron (MLP) Intrusion Detection System (IDS) optimized using Particle Swarm Optimization (PSO). The framework is designed for IoT cybersecurity environments where preserving the privacy of sensitive network traffic is critical.
The proposed methodology integrates:
•	Deep Learning based Intrusion Detection
•	Differential Privacy using DP-SGD
•	Particle Swarm Optimization for Hyperparameter Tuning
•	Stratified Cross Validation
•	Privacy–Utility Trade-off Evaluation
•	TensorFlow Privacy Framework
The implementation supports reproducible experiments suitable for Springer journal submission and peer-review evaluation.
________________________________________
2. Research Contributions
The study contributes the following:
1.	Development of a privacy-preserving IDS using Differential Privacy.
2.	Integration of PSO for automated hyperparameter optimization.
3.	Evaluation of privacy-utility trade-offs under DP-SGD.
4.	Comparison between non-private and private deep learning models.
5.	Computation of formal privacy guarantees using epsilon (ε) and delta (δ).
6.	Experimental validation using IoT intrusion datasets.
________________________________________
3. Methodology
The proposed framework consists of the following stages:
Stage 1: Data Preprocessing
•	Dataset loading
•	Feature normalization using StandardScaler
•	Label encoding of attack classes
•	Train-validation-test splitting
Stage 2: PSO Hyperparameter Optimization
PSO optimizes:
•	Number of hidden layers
•	Number of neurons
•	Dropout rates
•	Learning rate
•	Batch size
•	Activation functions
•	Optimizer selection
•	Epoch configuration
Stage 3: Deep Learning IDS Training
Two models are trained:
Non-Private Model
Standard SGD/Adam optimization without privacy.
Private Model
DP-SGD optimization using:
•	Gradient clipping
•	Gaussian noise injection
•	Privacy accounting
Stage 4: Evaluation
Performance metrics:
•	Accuracy
•	Precision
•	Recall
•	F1-score
•	Precision-Recall AUC
•	Confusion Matrix
Privacy metrics:
•	Privacy Budget ε (epsilon)
•	Delta δ
•	Noise Multiplier
•	Gradient Clipping Norm
